. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The Israelites said to Samuel, “Don’t stop crying out to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" our God for us, so that he will save us from the Philistines.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Samuel took a young lamb "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lv 22:27","book":"Lev","chapter":22,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and offered it as a whole burnt offering to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". He cried out to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" on behalf of Israel, and the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" answered him. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 99:6","book":"Psa","chapter":99,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 15:1","book":"Jer","chapter":15,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lv 22:27","book":"Lev","chapter":22,"verse":27},{"label":"Ps 99:6","book":"Psa","chapter":99,"verse":6},{"label":"Jr 15:1","book":"Jer","chapter":15,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel was offering the burnt offering as the Philistines approached to fight against Israel. The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" thundered loudly "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 2:10","book":"1Sa","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 22:14","book":"2Sa","chapter":22,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" against the Philistines that day and threw them into such confusion that they were defeated by Israel. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 23:27","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":27,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 10:10","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":10,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 4:15","book":"Jdg","chapter":4,"verse":15,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 2:10","book":"1Sa","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"2Sm 22:14","book":"2Sa","chapter":22,"verse":14},{"label":"Ex 23:27","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":27},{"label":"Jos 10:10","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":10},{"label":"Jdg 4:15","book":"Jdg","chapter":4,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then the men of Israel charged out of Mizpah and pursued the Philistines striking them down all the way to a place below Beth-car."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Afterward, Samuel took a stone and set it upright "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 4:9","book":"Jos","chapter":4,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" between Mizpah and Shen. He named it Ebenezer, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"= Stone of Help"},{"kind":"text","text":" explaining, “The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" has helped us to this point.” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 4:9","book":"Jos","chapter":4,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"= Stone of Help"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So the Philistines were subdued "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 13:1–15","book":"Jdg","chapter":13,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"LXX reads The Lord humbled the Philistines and they"},{"kind":"text","text":" did not invade Israel’s territory again. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 13:5","book":"1Sa","chapter":13,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s hand was against the Philistines all of Samuel’s life. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jdg 13:1–15","book":"Jdg","chapter":13,"verse":1},{"label":"1Sm 13:5","book":"1Sa","chapter":13,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"LXX reads The Lord humbled the Philistines and they"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The cities from Ekron to Gath, which they had taken from Israel, were restored; Israel even rescued their surrounding territories from Philistine control. There was also peace between Israel and the Amorites."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Samuel judged Israel throughout his life. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 7:6","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 12:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 7:6","book":"1Sa","chapter":7,"verse":6},{"label":"1Sm 12:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Every year he would go on a circuit to Bethel, Gilgal, and Mizpah and would judge Israel at all these locations. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Sa:7:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then he would return to Ramah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 1:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 1:19","book":"1Sa","chapter":1,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 2:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":2,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" because his home was there, he judged Israel there, and he built an altar to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" there."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 1:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":1,"verse":1},{"label":"1Sm 1:19","book":"1Sa","chapter":1,"verse":19},{"label":"1Sm 2:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":2,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783099287208}